President Joseph R. Biden held a conversation with Transatlantic leaders regarding the potential for increased Russian aggression against Ukraine. They expressed deep concern over Russia's ongoing military build-up, reaffirmed their strong support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, and discussed the importance of providing further economic assistance to Ukraine. The leaders pledged to continue diplomatic efforts to de-escalate tensions while remaining prepared to impose swift and coordinated economic consequences on Russia if it escalates the conflict. They also discussed measures to ensure the defense and security of NATO's eastern flank. The participants in the call included Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada, European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen, European Council President Charles Michel, President Emmanuel Macron of France, Chancellor Olaf Scholz of Germany, Prime Minister Mario Draghi of Italy, NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg, President Andrzej Duda of Poland, President Klaus Iohannis of Romania, and Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom.